headlines.description: Jake Wright never shot inside the 3-point arc and buried a career-high seven 3s for a career-high 22 points and Miami (Ohio) beat Fort Wayne 81-73 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright's 3-assault leads Miami (OH) past Fort Wayne 81-73

headlines.description: Dru Smith scored 17 points with six assists to lead Evansville as it beat Canisius 65-58 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith with 17 points as Evansville beats Canisius 65-58

headlines.description: Tayler Persons scored 23 points, including seven straight down the stretch and the game-winning 3-pointer with 3.3 seconds left, and Ball State beat Valparaiso 71-70 on Saturday to win its fifth straight.
headlines.shortLinkText: Person's last-second 3 lifts Ball St over Valparaiso 71-70

headlines.description: Isaiah Williams and Jeff Thomas each scored 15 points and Georgia State fought off Montana at the end for a 71-68 win on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia State holds off Montana's late rally, wins 71-68

headlines.description: Eddie Keith II gained his first double-double, Zane Martin scored 15 points and sparked a 9-1 run as Towson broke open a tight game to defeat crosstown rival, Maryland-Baltimore County 78-65 Saturday and earn its tenth-straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towson rallies past UMBC for 10th-straight win 78-65

headlines.description: Donte Grantham scored 16 of his 20 points in the second half to lead the Tigers to an 81-59 victory over Samford on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grantham, Mitchell lift Clemson over Samford 81-59

headlines.description: Kevon Harris scored a career-high 31 points and Stephen F. Austin forced 27 turnovers to beat Rice 81-62 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris scores 31, leads Stephen F. Austin past Rice 81-62

headlines.description: Daniel Amigo scored 21 points with 10-for-12 shooting and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Denver to an 84-69 win over South Carolina Upstate on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Amigo powers Denver past SC Upstate 84-69

headlines.description: Devin Sibley scored 24 points, John Davis III added 21 and Furman rolled to a 101-72 victory over South Carolina State on Saturday.
Bruno Skokna scored 18 points with 4-for-5 shooting, Donte Ingram sank five 3-pointers and Loyola-Chicago cruised to an 80-52 win over winless Norfolk State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Loyola-Chicago cruises to 80-52 win over Norfolk State

headlines.description: Jalone Friday was on the mark Saturday, scoring 22 points and adding a career-best five blocked shots to lead Abilene Christian to a 72-68 victory over Texas State.
headlines.shortLinkText: Friday spurs Abilene Christian to 72-68 win over Texas State

headlines.description: Josh Nzeakor and reserve Nick Garth scored 18 points apiece and Lamar doubled up Division-III member Howard Payne 112-56 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lamar doubles up D-III member Howard Payne 112-56

headlines.description: JD Notae had 14 points, 10 rebounds and six assists as Jacksonville thumped Florida National 89-51 to stop a three-game losing skid on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Notae with 14 points, 10 boards leads Jacksonville to win

headlines.description: David Nichols scored 12 points and made two free throws in the final seconds to seal Albany's 74-69 win over Siena in the Albany Cup on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Albany holds on for 10th win, beats Siena 74-69

headlines.description: Freshman Keaton Wallace made five 3-pointers and scored a career-high 24 and Byron Frohnen added 18 points and eight rebounds to spark UT San Antonio to an 87-71 victory over Houston Baptist on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: UT San Antonio cruises past Houston Baptist 87-71

headlines.description: Khalil Ahmad ripped the nets for a career-high 34 points, burying 6 of 10 tries from 3-point range, and Cal State Fullerton held off Utah Valley 91-83 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ahmad scores 34 as CS Fullerton cools off Utah Valley 91-83

headlines.description: TJ Haws scored a season-high 24 points as BYU defeated Weber State 74-68 on Saturday night in the second game of the inaugural Beehive Classic.
headlines.shortLinkText: Haws scores season-high 24, BYU beats Weber State 74-68

headlines.description: Damiyne Durham had 19 points and three steals and Rickey Holden scored six of his 10 points in the final five minutes to help CSU Bakersfield hold on for a 66-55 win over Idaho on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Durham, Holden help CSUB beat Idaho 66-55

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
